<subsection xml:id="summary-of-factoring">
  <title>Summary of Factoring <m>ax^2 + bx + c</m></title>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        If there is a common factor among all of the terms, factor out the greatest common factor (GCF).
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          If the leading coefficient (the number in front of <m>x^2</m>) is negative, factor out <m>-1</m> from all terms (basically, flip the sign of each term).
        </li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        <ol marker="(a)">
          <li>
            If <m>a = 1</m> (<m>x^2 + bx + c</m>), find two numbers that multiply to <m>c</m> and add to <m>b</m>.
          </li>
          <li>
            If <m>a \neq 1</m> (<m>ax^2 + bx + c</m>), use the cross method.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      (Optional) To check your answer, you can expand (FOIL) and check if you get back the original expression.
    </li>
  </ol>
</subsection>
